---
import ServicePage from '../layouts/ServicePage.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<ServicePage
  title="Local SEO Manchester & Stockport | MM SEO"
  description="Local SEO specialist in Stockport. GBP optimisation, local citations, geo-targeted content for Manchester and the UK."
  canonical="https://www.mmseo.co.uk/local-seo/"
  breadcrumb="Local SEO"
>

  <!-- ── 1. Hero band (dark) ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-hero-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Local SEO — Manchester, Stockport &amp; UK</p>
      <h1 class="sp-h1">Local SEO — Be Found When It Matters Most</h1>
      <p class="sp-intro">
        When your customers search for businesses like yours in your area, you need to
        appear — in the map pack, in organic results, and on the right terms. Local SEO
        is the set of strategies that makes that happen, and it's where I've helped
        businesses in Manchester, Stockport, and across the UK consistently win
        against larger, better-funded competitors.
      </p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">Book a Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 2. Main content (light) ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">What Local SEO Involves</h2>

      <p>
        Local SEO is distinct from general organic SEO in that it focuses on ranking
        in geographic searches — "SEO consultant Manchester", "solicitor Stockport",
        "hair salon near me". These searches have extremely high commercial intent,
        which makes local visibility directly tied to enquiries and footfall.
      </p>
      <p>
        The local search ecosystem has three main components: your Google Business
        Profile, your on-site geo-targeted content, and your local citations and
        links. All three need to be strong and consistent for you to compete
        effectively in the map pack and local organic results.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3">What I do</h3>
      <ul class="sp-list">
        <li><strong>Google Business Profile optimisation</strong> — complete profile setup, category selection, service areas, Q&amp;A, photo strategy, and ongoing management</li>
        <li><strong>NAP consistency audit</strong> — ensuring your Name, Address, and Phone number are consistent across every directory, citation, and listing online</li>
        <li><strong>Local citation building</strong> — strategic submissions to relevant UK business directories and industry-specific platforms</li>
        <li><strong>Geo-targeted on-site content</strong> — location pages and service-area content written for both rankings and conversion</li>
        <li><strong>Local keyword strategy</strong> — mapping geo-specific search terms (near me, city+service) to pages on your site</li>
        <li><strong>Local link acquisition</strong> — building links from local newspapers, business associations, chambers of commerce, and community sites</li>
        <li><strong>Review generation strategy</strong> — a practical approach to ethically generating more Google reviews, which directly influence local pack rankings</li>
        <li><strong>Competitor benchmarking</strong> — understanding exactly what the businesses above you are doing and identifying the gaps we can close</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 3. Why it matters (dark) ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-why section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-why-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2 chalk">Why Local SEO Is a Different Game</h2>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Local search results are heavily weighted towards proximity, prominence, and
        relevance. A business that has optimised its Google Business Profile and
        built consistent local citations will routinely outrank a larger competitor
        with a stronger national presence — because Google's algorithm for local
        results prioritises trust signals that are specific to the local context.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        The map pack — the three Google Business listings that appear before organic
        results — captures a significant share of clicks for local searches. For many
        businesses, appearing in the map pack is more valuable than ranking number
        one organically. I optimise for both, but the map pack is often where the
        fastest wins are found.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        I'm based in Marple, Stockport and work extensively with businesses in
        Manchester, Stockport, and the wider Greater Manchester area — though my
        local SEO work extends across the UK. My own local SEO experience means I
        practise exactly what I preach.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 4. Contact CTA ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <ContactForm />

</ServicePage>

<style>
  .section-dark  { background-color: var(--ink);  color: var(--chalk); }
  .section-light { background-color: var(--chalk); color: var(--ink); }

  .container {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 2rem);
  }

  .sp-hero { padding: 5rem 0 4rem; }
  .sp-hero-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sp-h1 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--chalk);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sp-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background-color: var(--accent-dk); }

  .sp-content { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-content-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-h2 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-h2.chalk { color: var(--chalk); }

  .sp-h3 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .sp-content p, .sp-content-inner p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }

  .sp-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }
  .sp-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .sp-why { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-why-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .chalk { color: var(--chalk); }
  .chalk-muted {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
  }

  .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(24px);
    transition: opacity 0.55s ease, transform 0.55s ease;
  }
  .reveal.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: none;
  }
</style>

<script>
  const revealEls = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); io.unobserve(e.target); } }),
    { threshold: 0.12 }
  );
  revealEls.forEach(el => io.observe(el));
</script>
